17/01/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police in Republika Srpska (RS) announced on Wednesday (January 16th) they questioned 25 people last year who are suspected of helping war crimes fugitive Radovan Karadzic escape justice. In a report sent to The Hague war crimes tribunal, officials said the suspects were questioned between July and September 2007. The goal was to exert pressure on suspected supporters, identified as people from all social categories in RS, Serbia and Montenegro. Former BiH presidency member Mirko Sarovic was among those questioned. (Balkaninsight, NTV Hayat, SRNA, RTRS, Dnevni Avaz, Fena - 16/01/08)
